b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe3231.htm)  [Next](sbe3233.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0543968677/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_Vedic Hymns, Part I (SBE32)_ , by Max Muller, [1891], at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 293\n\n### MA _N_ _D_ ALA I, HYMN 172.\n\n#### ASH _T_ AKA II, ADHY\xc3\x82YA 4, VARGA 12.\n\n#### To the Maruts (the Storm-gods).\n\n1\\. May your march be brilliant, brilliant through your protection, O Maruts,\nyou bounteous givers, shining like snakes!\n\n2\\. May that straightforward shaft of yours, O Maruts, bounteous givers, be\nfar from us, and far the stone which you hurl!\n\n3\\. Spare, O bounteous givers, the people of T _ri_ _n_ askanda, lift us up\nthat we may live!\n\np. 294\n\n#### NOTES.\n\nThe hymn is ascribed to Agastya, the metre is Gayatri. None of its verses\noccurs in SV., VS., TS., AV.\n\n##### Verse 1.\n\nProf. Oldenberg conjectures _k_ itra\xc2\xb4 uti _h_ , and possibly mahibhanava _h_\nfor ahibhanava _h_. See for ya\xc2\xb4ma _h_ _k_ itra _h_ uti\xc2\xb4 V, 52, 2. te ya\xc2\xb4man\npanti; also VI, 48, 9.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: II, 34. To the Maruts (the Storm-gods)](sbe3233.htm)\n\n'